```
2. Initialize a priority queue and a distance map to keep track of the shortest distance from the starting node to each node in the graph, with the initial distance of the starting node set to 0 and all other distances set to infinity.
```java
    PriorityQueue<Pair<String, Integer>> pq = new PriorityQueue<>(Comparator.comparingInt(Pair::getValue));
    Map<String, Integer> distance = new HashMap<>();
    for (String node : graph.keySet()) {
        distance.put(node, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
    }
    distance.put(arr[1], 0);
    pq.offer(new Pair<>(arr[1], 0));
```
3. Repeat the following until the priority queue is empty:
   - Dequeue a node (let's call it `u`) from the priority queue
   - For each neighbor `v` of `u`, if the distance from starting node to `v` through `u` is shorter than the current distance in the distance map, update the distance and add `v` to the priority queue with the updated distance.
```java
    while (!pq.isEmpty()) {
        Pair<String, Integer> node = pq.poll();
        String u = node.getKey();
        int dist = node.getValue();
        if (dist > distance.get(u)) {
            continue;
        }
        for (Pair<String, Integer> neighbor : graph.get(u)) {
            String v = neighbor.getKey();
            int alt = dist + neighbor.getValue();
            if (alt < distance.get(v)) {
                distance.put(v, alt);
                pq.offer(new Pair<>(v, alt));
            }
        }
    }
```
4. Return the shortest distance from the starting node to the ending node, or -1 if there is no path between them.
```java
    int dist = distance.get(arr[arr.length - 1]);
    return dist == Integer.MAX_VALUE ? -1 : dist;
```

Putting it all together, the solution looks like this:
```java
public static int shortestPath(String[] arr) {
    int n = Integer.parseInt(arr[0]);
    Map<String, List<Pair<String, Integer>>> graph = new HashMap<>();
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        graph.put(arr[i], new ArrayList<>());
    }
    for (int i = n + 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
        String[] connection = arr[i].split("-");
        int weight = 1; // assume weight of each edge is equal to 1
        graph.get(connection[0]).add(new Pair<>(connection[1], weight));
        graph.get(connection[1]).add(new Pair<>(connection[0], weight));
    }
    PriorityQueue<Pair<String, Integer>> pq = new PriorityQueue<>(Comparator.comparingInt(Pair::getValue));
    Map<String, Integer> distance = new HashMap<>();
    for (String node : graph.keySet()) {
        distance.put(node, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
    }
    distance.put(arr[1], 0);
    pq.offer(new Pair<>(arr[1], 0));
    while (!pq.isEmpty()) {
        Pair<String, Integer> node = pq.poll();
        String u = node.getKey();
        int dist = node.getValue();
        if (dist > distance.get(u)) {
            continue;
        }
        for (Pair<String, Integer> neighbor : graph.get(u)) {
            String v = neighbor.getKey();
            int alt = dist + neighbor.getValue();
            if (alt < distance.get(v)) {
                distance.put(v, alt);
                pq.offer(new Pair<>(v, alt));
            }
        }
    }
    int dist = distance.get(arr[arr.length - 1]);
    return dist == Integer.MAX_VALUE ? -1 : dist;
}
```

